{"symbol": "MED15", "uniprot": "Q96RN5", "protein_name": "Mediator of RNA polymerase II transcription subunit 15", "length": 788, "function": "Component of the Mediator complex, a coactivator involved in the regulated transcription of nearly all RNA polymerase II-dependent genes. Mediator functions as a bridge to convey information from gene-specific regulatory proteins to the basal RNA polymerase II transcription machinery. Mediator is recruited to promoters by direct interactions with regulatory proteins and serves as a scaffold for the assembly of a functional preinitiation complex with RNA polymerase II and the general transcription factors. Required for cholesterol-dependent gene regulation. Positively regulates the Nodal signaling pathway", "ensembl_gene": "ENSG00000099917", "scores": {"selectivity": 0.5536, "protein_drug": 0.405, "rna_drug": 0.455}, "flags": {"surface": false, "enzyme": true, "mod_aso": true, "mod_sirna": false}, "details": {"nominated_modality": "ASO", "winning_axis": "RNA", "quadrant": "Both viable", "best_route": "small molecule", "sm_score": "0.497", "sirna_score": "0.086", "aso_score": "0.36"}, "modality": "ASO", "structure": "data/structures/MED15.pdb", "pockets": [{"rank": 1, "druggability": 0.592, "volume": 282.2, "residues": [674, 678, 679, 682, 683, 691, 692, 693, 704, 706]}, {"rank": 2, "druggability": 0.29, "volume": 463.0, "residues": [542, 545, 548, 549, 551, 552, 596, 598, 599, 600, 601]}, {"rank": 3, "druggability": 0.25, "volume": 341.6, "residues": [220, 223, 224, 226, 227, 230]}], "links": [{"key": "uniprot", "label": "UniProt", "url": "https://www.uniprot.org/uniprotkb/Q96RN5"}, {"key": "alphafold", "label": "AlphaFold", "url": "https://alphafold.ebi.ac.uk/entry/Q96RN5"}, {"key": "opentargets", "label": "Open Targets", "url": "https://platform.opentargets.org/target/ENSG00000099917"}, {"key": "genecards", "label": "GeneCards", "url": "https://www.genecards.org/cgi-bin/carddisp.pl?gene=MED15"}, {"key": "ensembl", "label": "